          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>halved tomatoes</strong> and<strong> torn bread </strong>to a bowl with your <strong>dried basil</strong>, 2 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[3 tbsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[4 tbsp]</span> <strong>olive oil</strong> and a generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong></p><p>Mash the<strong> tomatoes</strong> together with the <strong>torn bread </strong>so that the juice soaks into the bread – these are your<strong> tomato croutons</strong></p>",
